# Figma MCP → AIRGÉ implementation plan

Use when analyzing Figma with the MCP. Produce an **implementation-ready markdown breakdown**. Prefer editing existing `src/sections/*` and `src/components/*` — see `project-conventions.mdc`.

Skill: `.cursor/skills/figma-mcp-section-analysis/SKILL.md`  
Icons: `ICONS_CANVA_GUIDE.md`, barrel `src/assets/icons/index.js`

## Required output

### Sections concerned

- Map to `src/sections/*` and anchor `id` (home: `#home`, `#probleme`, `#solution`, `#fonctionnalites`, `#impact`, `#tarifs`, `#faq`, `#cta-final`).

### Components

Per section:

- **Reuse**: `src/components/*` (path)
- **Create**: only if necessary (name + path)
- **Props**: brief data shape

### Assets

- Type, target path (`src/assets/images/*` or `src/assets/icons/*`), filename (kebab-case), usage.

### Icons required (if any)

Per icon: purpose, filename, `src/assets/icons/`, where used, Figma node name, export spec (default **24×24**, ~2px padding, **2px stroke** outline).

### Tokens & layout

- Tailwind/`index.css` token updates (`airge-*`) — no vague “update styling”.
- Note if `navLinks` / section `id` must stay in sync.

## Guardrails

- **Reuse** over **Create** when a section/component already exists.
- No new layout system; keep `padding*`, `max-container`, breakpoints.
- Home section order lives in `src/pages/Landing.jsx` — do not reorder without explicit request.
- Hero: ship without new hero image unless requested.
